        "username": "weibao",
        "uid": "41372"
      },
      "contents": "<div class=\"markitup-box aw-briefly\">\n\t\t\thttps://www.theguardian.com/science/2022/oct/16/ultra-processed-food-unhealthier-harder-to-avoid-than-you-thought<br/>\n<br/>\n<blockquote>NOVA (not an acronym) is a widely used food classification system that separates foods into four categories based upon their level of processing. Almost all foods, aside from fresh fruit and raw vegetables, undergo some degree of process. Cooking is a process, and it usually involves added ingredients such as oil and salt.<br/>\n<br/>\nIn NOVA’s first category, Group 1 is unprocessed or minimally processed foods (fruit, vegetables, meat, eggs, milk). Group 2 is made up of processed culinary ingredients such as sugars, oils and butter. Group 3 is processed foods (canned vegetables and fish, bread, jam). Group 4 is ultra-high processed foods, which are mostly low in protein and fibre, and high in salt, sugar and fat, and have undergone industrial interventions such as extrusion, moulding and milling.<br/>\n<br/>\n...<br/>\n<br/>\nThere is very clear observational data showing that <b>people who have higher intakes of ultra-processed foods have higher levels of ill-health, whether it be cancer, cardiovascular disease, high blood pressure, obesity or type 2 diabetes.</b></blockquote><br/>\n<br/>\n推预制菜估计是推广国有海克斯科技的政策一环，背后可能已经有一个完整的土匪家族控股的产业链，<br/>\n<br/>\n各种添加剂，佐料，地沟油，都是化工产品的消费终端，<br/>\n<br/>\n牠们是不会衡量吃食（屎）者的健康，只会赚黑心钱的一帮掌权人，<br/>\n<br/>\n预制菜只是为普通人下定决心润更增添一条理由？？\t\t<div class=\"aw-stretch-content-button-container\"><button class=\"aw-stretch-content-button\" type=\"button\"></button></div></div>",
      "date": "2023-08-29",
      "agree_count": 4,
      "discussion_count": 3,
